notesStmt.note: Dimensions of original manuscript: 155 x 95 (100 x 50) mm bound to 160 x 100 mm.

msIdentifier.repository: University of Pennsylvania Museum of Archaeology and Anthropology

msContents.summary: Collection of doxologies and prayers, ascribed to ʻAlī or to his grandson Zayn al-ʻĀbidin ʻAlī ibn al-Ḥusayn with Persian interlinear translation and marginal notes; a leaf has been cut out between f. 25 and 26.

respStmt.persName: ʻAlī ibn Abī Ṭālib, Caliph, approximately 600-661

supportDesc.foliation: Leaves are unfoliated; catchwords every verso, lower left.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 20 long lines with alternating lines of Arabic and Persian; Arabic lines are 3 mm taller than Persian lines; catchwords every verso, lower left (often trimmed); marginalia.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink (Arabic) and nastaʻlīq in red ink (Persian); pointed, with Arabic partially vocalized; marginalia in nastaʻlīq in black ink.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated headpiece in gold, blue, red and green with foliate marginal fill on first page-opening (f. 1v-2r); textblock is border-ruled in blue, red, gold, and blue with page-opening framed in narrow gold and black; lines are ruled in narrow gold and black

binding.p: Bound in reddish brown leather over pasteboard with inlay, blind-stamped central mandorla with two pendants on the vertical axis; edges of cover and spine in red leather; black leather doublure.

origin.p: Copy completed in Rajab of the year 1107 (February 1696) (f. [150]r).

history.provenance: Gift of the Ralph Foster Museum in 1994.
